# .antigravity: AI Context Rules for Shift Drift / Asteroid

## Project Overview
* Name: Shift Drift (internal code name: Asteroid)
* Type: Technical Showcase / Browser-based arcade refactor
* Status: Modern refactor of classic Asteroids focusing on AI-driven orchestration
* Stack: Vite, Vue 3, Supabase, Vercel, Vanilla Canvas 2D, Web Audio API
* Entry point: index.html -> src/game/main.js
* Deployment: Vercel (vercel.json)

## Source Layout
```
src/
  game/
    main.js        # Game loop, input handling, state machine (core logic)
    Ship.js        # Player ship: movement, combat, shields, theme handling
    Rival.js       # AI archenemy ship: adaptive behavior, same API as Ship
    Asteroid.js    # Asteroid entities: fragmentation logic
    Bullet.js      # Projectile physics
    Ufo.js         # Secondary enemy entity
    particles.js   # Visual effect systems
    audio.js       # Web Audio API implementation
    ui.js          # HUD, score systems, legal modals
    constants.js   # Production constants and magic numbers
    utils.js       # Mathematical utility functions
  landing/         # Vue-based technical showcase landing page
  styles/          # Modular CSS architecture
public/            # Static assets (images, videos, manifests)
```

## AI Interaction Guidelines
* Technical Tone: Maintain a professional, technical, and grounded tone in all communications.
* Stylistic Constraints: Never use em-dashes (—). Use colons, commas, or parentheses instead. No emojis in technical documentation.
* No Indents: Maintain a flat structure in documentation (README/etc) as requested by the user.
* Targeted Edits: Use multi_replace_file_content for non-contiguous changes; replace_file_content for single contiguous blocks.
* Minimal Reads: Only read files relevant to the current task to conserve context.
* Dev Server: npm run dev starts the local environment on port 5173.
* Check constants.js: Verify existing technical parameters before introducing new ones.
* Austrian Law Compliance: Adhere to DSGVO/GDPR requirements for legal texts (Impressum/Datenschutz).

## Technical Orchestration
* Core Logic: Managed in main.js via a reactive state object.
* Theme System: Toggle-based rendering using the isRetro flag.
* Persistence: Global leaderboards integrated via Supabase.
* Hosting: Edge-optimized delivery via Vercel.

## Common Task Mapping
| Task | Primary File(s) |
|---|---|
| Physics / Game Constants | constants.js, main.js |
| Player Mechanics | Ship.js |
| Rival AI / Mechanics | Rival.js |
| Audio Synthesis | audio.js |
| HUD / UI Components | ui.js, src/landing/ |
| Persistence / Database | src/landing/ (modal handles info) |
| Build / Deploy | vite.config.js, vercel.json |
